### Okta credential stuffing seed data — Elastic Security demo
#
# Requires an HTTP client that supports the {{$datetime iso8601 -N m}}
# dynamic variable (VS Code "REST Client" extension, or IntelliJ/WebStorm's
# built-in HTTP Client) — timestamps are computed at SEND time so the data
# always lands inside the rule/preview window.
#
# Fill in the variables below from Terraform outputs / shared/env.json:
#   terraform -chdir=terraform output -raw elasticsearch_url
#   terraform -chdir=terraform output -raw elastic_password
#
# Idempotent: send request #1 (delete-by-query) before every take, then
# requests #2 and #3, so re-runs never stack duplicate demo events.
#
# Attack chain seeded for jsmith@example.com from the attacker IP:
#   Stage 1 — 5 failed logins (INVALID_CREDENTIALS)
#   Stage 2 — 2 MFA push failures (FACTOR_CHALLENGE_TIMEOUT)
#   Stage 3 — 1 successful login
#   Stage 4 — 1 privilege grant (post-compromise)
# bjones and alee get Stage 1 only (no MFA, no success — rule stays quiet).
# mwilson (benign IP) has 1 failed + 1 success — forgot password, no MFA failures.

@esUrl = https://CHANGE-ME.es.CHANGE-ME.cloud.es.io
@esUser = elastic
@esPassword = CHANGE-ME

@attackerIp = 203.0.113.66
@benignIp = 198.51.100.20


### 1. Clear any previous take's demo events for these two source IPs
POST {{esUrl}}/logs-okta.system-default/_delete_by_query?refresh=true&conflicts=proceed
Authorization: Basic {{esUser}} {{esPassword}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": {
    "terms": {
      "source.ip": ["{{attackerIp}}", "{{benignIp}}"]
    }
  }
}


### 2. Attacker IP — credential stuffing attack chain
# bjones (Stage 1 only: 3 failed logins — no MFA, no success, rule stays quiet)
# alee   (Stage 1 only: 2 failed logins — no MFA, no success, rule stays quiet)
# jsmith (full chain: 5 failed → 2 MFA failures → success → privilege grant → FIRES rule)
POST {{esUrl}}/logs-okta.system-default/_bulk?refresh=true
Authorization: Basic {{esUser}} {{esPassword}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"create":{}}
{"@timestamp":"{{$datetime iso8601 -45 m}}","event":{"action":"user.session.start","outcome":"failure","dataset":"okta.system","category":["authentication"],"kind":"event"},"okta":{"event_type":"user.session.start","outcome":{"result":"FAILURE","reason":"INVALID_CREDENTIALS"}},"source":{"ip":"{{attackerIp}}"},"client":{"ip":"{{attackerIp}}"},"user":{"name":"bjones@example.com","email":"bjones@example.com"},"data_stream":{"dataset":"okta.system","namespace":"default","type":"logs"}}
{"create":{}}
